Reasoning: The paper discusses reducing the complexity of a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for automatic classification of time-varying brightness data of stars to detect exoplanets. This involves examining two methods for complexity reduction in AstroNet, a CNN, and conducting experiments with various degrees of dropout regularization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper involves time-series data, cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) could also be a possible sub-category, although less likely than the others.
